:{{see|circinus}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille in 1763. From {{L.}} ''[[circinus]]'', a "pair of [[compass]]es"

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Circinus'''

#{{constellation}}: A small [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] [[winter]] sky, said to resemble a [[compass]]. It lies between the [[constellation]]s of [[Centaurus]] and [[Triangulum Australe]].

